Started out with great food and great service. Now the staff is unaware of pricing and is comfortable taking their time as they socialize ringing up an order. Ordered last night and this afternoon. Was given the pot scrapings of the left over rice that was all hard (not pegao....hard. Pot scraped. Rice.) I didnt even ask for pegao/concon and wasn't informed that was what was left or I would have ordered differently. Today I ordered pernil was given more than half of my order in fat. The bit of meat I did get was slightly pink and unseasoned. It tasted like boiled pork...not oven roasted or seasoned at all. I called to complain and was told 'it wasnt me' and that 'today's staff had nothing to do with last night's staff'. Had to ask for a manager/supervisor. So disappointed because the food was really good and the service was excellent every other time I've been/had delivery. Won't be eating from here again. To think....last time I started a 5 star review and was distracted before I posted it. Glad I didnt. Reeeeeally disappointed!
